[DQC.US.0189.10184] The filing has reported a value for the element us-gaap:DebtInstrumentBasisSpreadOnVariableRate1 with a value of 0.0184 using the axis VariableRateAxis in the role 100510 - Disclosure - Mortgage Notes and Credit Facility - Summary of Mortgage Notes and Credit Facility Secured by Company's Properties (Details) on the table us-gaap:DebtInstrumentTable. However, the only member used to disaggregate the total for us-gaap:DebtInstrumentBasisSpreadOnVariableRate1 was the member us-gaap:SecuredOvernightFinancingRateSofrOvernightIndexSwapRateMember. If only one member is used on this axis then the filer should either:
1. Retag the filing using the element InvestmentVariableInterestRateTypeExtensibleEnumeration or DebtInstrumentVariableInterestRateTypeExtensibleEnumeration with a value of us-gaap:SecuredOvernightFinancingRateSofrOvernightIndexSwapRateMember. The member us-gaap:SecuredOvernightFinancingRateSofrOvernightIndexSwapRateMember should be removed from the value as it represents the aggregate value of us-gaap:DebtInstrumentBasisSpreadOnVariableRate1.
2. Tag the aggregate value of us-gaap:DebtInstrumentBasisSpreadOnVariableRate1 with a value of 0.0184 without the VariableRateAxis axis. This rule will not generate an error if the aggregate value of us-gaap:DebtInstrumentBasisSpreadOnVariableRate1 is reported.
